      • FileTransferAuth

        public FileTransferAuth(String user,
                char[] password,
                String serviceUrl)
        Constructs authentication information for file transfer using long form of the user name.

        Use this method for UUID based URLs. But it can also be used for identity domain and service name based URLs. The long form of the user name is of the following format:

        • For UUID-based URLs:
          • service URL: https://[UUID].storage.oraclecloud.com
          • user: [UUID]:[UserName]
        • For identity-domain based URLs:
          • service URL: https://[IdentityDomain].storage.oraclecloud.com
          • user: [ServiceName]-[IdentityDomain]:[IdentityDomain].[UserName]
        Note: Replace the UUID, ServiceName, IdenityDomain, UserName with their actual values without the brackets. The UserName could be either the name of the user role or the user's e-mail address.
        Parameters:
        user - long form of the user name
        password - password for the user
        serviceUrl - service URL
